                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-11T14:00:00-03:50">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—6:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. At the meeting of the diplomatic corps today it was the unanimous opinion
                    that only the American Government could cause Bolivia to recognize its treaty
                    obligations and that its failure to do so would cause the Gondra Treaty and the
                    Kellogg Pact to be of no value.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kreeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
